** # Directions to installing your own Firmware **
Follow the following steps to ensure your board is recognised:
1. Install the Latest Version of Arduino IDE.
2. Open Arduino IDE → File → Preferences:
   In Additional Board Manager URLs, add "https://github.com/earlephilhower/arduino-pico/releases/download/global/package_rp2040_index.json"
   Go to Tools → Board → Board Manager.
   Search for RP2040 and install “Raspberry Pi RP2040 Boards by Earle Philhower”.
3. Open File Explorer and go to - "C:\Users\<Your Name>\AppData\Local\Arduino15\packages\rp2040\hardware\rp2040\5.4.4\variants" **(place your PC's username in place of "<Your Name>")**
4. Create your custom variant in .../variants/, create a new folder: "myboard".(instead of "myboard" enter a name that you like)
   Inside "myboard", create pins_arduino.h (you can copy and paste the file from a surrounding board file and edit it) and paste this:
" #pragma once

// ===== LED =====
#define PIN_LED         25
#ifndef LED_BUILTIN
#define LED_BUILTIN     PIN_LED
#endif

// ===== UART =====
#define PIN_SERIAL_TX   0     // USB/UART TX
#define PIN_SERIAL_RX   1     // USB/UART RX

// ===== I2C =====
#define PIN_WIRE_SDA    8
#define PIN_WIRE_SCL    9

// ===== SPI (LoRa SX1262) =====
#define PIN_SPI_SCK     2
#define PIN_SPI_MOSI    3
#define PIN_SPI_MISO    4
#define PIN_LORA_NSS    5     // Chip select
#define PIN_LORA_DIO1   6
#define PIN_LORA_BUSY   7
#define PIN_LORA_RESET  22

// ===== RF switch =====
#define PIN_RF_SWITCH   10

// ===== ADC =====
#define PIN_A0          26
#define PIN_A1          27
#define PIN_A2          28

// ===== Debug pins =====
#define PIN_SWCLK       24
#define PIN_SWDIO       25

// ===== Default interfaces =====
#define SERIAL_PORT_MONITOR   Serial
#define SERIAL_PORT_HARDWARE  Serial1 "

** #( Important Note: You have to check your scheamtic and enter the corresponding pin numbers, I have added these according to mine, if you are not sure about your pin numbers you may attach a screenshot of your scheamtics to AI and ask it for the pin numbers. )**
5. Find the "boards file in 'C:\Users\<Your Name>\AppData\Local\Arduino15\packages\rp2040\hardware\rp2040\5.4.4\'" **(place your PC's username in place of "<Your Name>")**
   Then paste this at the very end **DO NOT ERASE ANYTHING ELSE**: 
"
loraboard.name=<Your Name>
loraboard.build.core=rp2040
loraboard.build.variant=lora_board
loraboard.upload.maximum_size=2097152
loraboard.upload.maximum_data_size=262144
loraboard.upload.protocol=rp2040
loraboard.build.f_cpu=133000000L
loraboard.build.usb_product="RP2040 LoRa Board"
loraboard.build.usb_manufacturer="<Your Name>"
" **(place your desired name(s) in place of "<Your Name>")**
6. Close and open Arduino IDE, then go to tools -> Board -> Raspberry Pi Pico /RP2040 -> find your board and Upload your sketch!
